Usage:
---------------------------------------------
StudentTracker <flags> <arguments>

Example:
    To list all students in the "NSA" class use:
        
        StudetnTracker -ls -c 1 


FLAGS:
    DATABASE:
        -cd <db_file_name>
            Create a New Databse
        
        -rd <db_file_name>
            Remove Database
        -ld
            List database files

    LIST:
        -lc
            Lists All avalible classes.
            If a moddifier is added it wil list a spesific class.

        -ls 
            Lists avalible students.
            With no other arguments lists all students over all classes.
        
        -li
            Lists information about a class or student.

    MODIFIERS:
        -c 
            Defines what class to target.
        
        -s 
            Defines what student to target.
        
        -d 
            Defines what day to target.
        
